title: Jesuit High Volleyball Team wins national tournament
text:
Jesuit High Volleyball Team wins national tournament The Jesuit girls volleyball team won the Nike Tournament of Champions over the weekend. Post to Facebook Jesuit High Volleyball Team wins national tournament The Jesuit girls volleyball team won the Nike Tournament of Champions over the weekend.  //on.kgw.com/1RrjSFC   Jesuit High Volleyball Team wins national tournament Art Edwards, KGW Staff 1:11 p.m. PDT October 5, 2015 The 2015 Jesuit Varsity Volleyball team. (Photo: KGW) 
PORTLAND, Ore. -- The Jesuit girls volleyball team won the Nike Tournament of Champions over the weekend. 
Jesuit went into the tournament ranked #5 in the nation. 
In the title game the Crusaders beat P.K. Yonge High School from Gainesville, Florida, the defending Florida state champions and the #2 team in the country. 
Jesuit is the defending Oregon 6A champion. They finished last season undefeated and are 18-0 this year. 
Jesuit plays Aloha in a metro league match Tuesday evening.
